rComments: overall she's a good professor. She taught me what I needed to know to do well in the course. I just didn't like how she lectured for 2 hours straight. TAKE PROPER NOTES IN CLASS you'll screw yourself over if you don't. assignments/essay r a breeze. midterm/ final r not bad. just take notes!! seriously, extensive notes bc her slides only have pics
Prof Kim just repeats facts but doesnt seem to care about the art shes talking about. Also unreasonable of her to expect us to know the entire history of Greek mythology in an intro course.
If students wanted to study Philosophy of Time, they would apply to study Philosophy, not Art History. She is taking up space from someone who could teach true Art History.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Participation matters', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Like others have said she expects us to have a deep understanding of Greek mythology even though this is an introductory course. Her lectures are ok but a bit disorganized. She isnt very knowledgable on Greek art and nowhere near as passionate as other professors in the department.
She teaches everything: astrophysics, art history, Greek art, Gandhara art, women and gender, philosophy of time. She is not a real Art History professor and she should not work here.
Prof Kim is a great and responsible lecturer. She is very specific with her expectation and it's not difficult to get an A if you follow the class.

Awesome prof. Very knowledgeable and and enthusiastic lectures that are easy to absorb. The assignments are fun and she often offers opportunities for extra credit. I'm not the greatest student and even I learned a lot. Took a couple of her classes and can confirm how consistently enjoyable her lectures are.

For an intro level course, she put too many expectations for her students. Most students took this class because they needed to fulfill their breath requirements or were just interested in Greek & Rome art, but she saw them as experienced students in the area. Don't know much about Greek and Rome mythology and history? Definitely got lost in class

Professor Kim is not only one of the best lecturers I have ever had, but also is probably one of the easiest markers. Show up to class, pay attention, and do all the work on time and I don't see how getting an A+ in the course is not possible. I will definitely be taking future courses with Prof Kim!
